      "content": "When addressing disruptive behavior, focus strictly on the *impact* of the actions, not the person's character. Instead of saying \"You are disruptive,\" use objective language like, \"Interjections during meetings frequently derail the agenda and impede team focus.\" You can frame it as a need for behavioral adjustment to better support group dynamics. This keeps the feedback professional and actionable, focusing on observable conduct.",
